{"lemma":"زِفْتٌ","slug":"زِفْتٌ","root":"ز.ف.ت","root_slug":"ز-ف-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-ف-ت","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n17862"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%90%D9%81%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pitch, tar, latex, asphalt"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to smear pitch onto"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Of uncertain ultimate origin. Related to Jewish Palestinian Aramaic, Jewish Literary Aramaic, Jewish Babylonian Aramaic זִפתָּא (zip̄tā) / זִיפתָּא (zip̄tā), Classical Syriac ܙܦܬܐ (zep̄tā), ܙܒܬܐ (zeḇtā), Hebrew זֶפֶת (zéfeṯ), possibly Arabic-borrowed Ge'ez ዝፍት (zəft) and Semitic-borrowed Old Armenian ձիւթ (jiwtʻ) and Old Georgian ძივთი (ʒivti). Neo-Babylonian 𒍣𒅁𒌈 (zi-ib-tum /⁠ziptu, zibtu⁠/), once glossed “pitch” and rare enough to be West Semitic borrowing, is more correctly glossed “a stone”.\n\nDenominal verb of زِفْت (zift)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n17862","headword_ar":"زِفْتٌ","root":"zft","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pitch:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tar:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of pitch:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crude pitch:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaArN","text_ar":"قَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, Mgh, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiyrN","text_ar":"قِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTiraAnN","text_ar":"قَطِرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, Msb:) or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiyrN","text_ar":"قِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiyr","text_ar":"قِير"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which ships are smeared, but"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like this inasmuch as"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is also a black substance, with which wine-skins are seasoned; for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qyr","text_ar":"قير"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of ships dries upon them, whereas the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zft","text_ar":"زفت"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of skins does not dry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crude pitch;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a produce of the pine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pitch-tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is of two sorts, moist and dry; the latter being either cooked, or congealed of itself;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as flows of itself from the trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zft","text_ar":"زفت"},{"kind":"text","text":"; such as is prepared by cooking, and art,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTiraAnN","text_ar":"قَطِرَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TK.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuforN","text_ar":"كُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see De Sacy's “ Abd-allatif, ” p. 273.] ―         -b2-  Also, (K, * TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zifotN","text_ar":"زِفْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muzaf~atN","text_ar":"مُزَفَّتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which Freytag has supposed to be here intended in the K, and not without some reason, for the passage is ambiguous,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain medicine;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that comes forth from the earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of bitumen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"perhaps another name for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaforN yahuwdiY~N","text_ar":"قَفْرٌ يَهُودِىٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bitumen Judaicum,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Jew's pitch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is an ingredient in medicines:"},{"kind":"text","text":"not the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zft","text_ar":"زفت"},{"kind":"text","text":"commonly known. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","Mgh","K","Msb","S","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}